                        <h3 style="font-size:30px  ;"><b>Workers Compensation in Western Australia</b></h3>

                        <p style="font-size: 17px;">If a person suffers from work-related injury or illness then he could be entitled to apply for claim as of workers compensation.</p>
                        <div class="tab">
                            <button class="tablinks" onclick="openCity(event, 'WA1')" id="defaultOpen">Eligibility</button>
                            <button class="tablinks" onclick="openCity(event, 'WA2')">Types of Claims</button>
                            <button class="tablinks" onclick="openCity(event, 'WA3')">Process to make a claim</button>
                        </div>

                        <div id="WA1" class="tabcontent">
                            <p style="text-align: left;">The eligible workers who can apply for claim are as follows,</p>
                            <ul style="text-align: left">
                                <li>Full-time</li>
                                <li>Part-time</li>
                                <li>Casual</li>
                            </ul>
                            <p style="text-align: left;"><b>Contractors and Sub-contractors</b> may be covered depending upon their work arrangements</p>
                            <br>
                            <p style="text-align: left;">For more detailed information please visit <a href="https://www.workcover.wa.gov.au/">Workcover WA</a></p>
                        </div>

                        <div id="WA2" class="tabcontent">

                            <p style="text-align: left;"><b>1.Statutory (no-fault) claim:</b> For statutory claims, compensation is paid regardless of who was at fault for causing the injury.</p>
                            <p style="text-align: left;">Payments and benefits received for this claim includes the following:</p>
                            <ul style="text-align: left">
                                <li>Weekly payments as income replacement</li>
                                <li>Lump sums to compensate for permanent impairment</li>
                                <li>Hospital and medical expenses</li>
                            </ul>
                            <br>
                            <p style="text-align: left;"><b>2.Common Law Claim:</b> If your injury is caused because of your employers negligence then you can apply for this claim. Common law claim can only proceed after a statutory claim has been lodged, and then accepted by WorkCover Western Australian or the relevant self-insurer.</p>
                            <p style="text-align: left;">Payments and benefits received for this claim includes the following:</p>
                            <ul style="text-align: left;">
                                <li>Economic Loss</li>
                                <li>Pain and Suffering</li>
                                <li>Legal Costs</li>
                                <li>Medical and Hospital Costs</li>
                            </ul>
                            <p style="text-align: left;">For more detailed information please visit <a href="https://www.workcover.wa.gov.au/">Workcover WA</a></p>
                        </div>

                        <div id="WA3" class="tabcontent">
